{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885953071,"sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0d23c10010h4qjkWizR8m7S","messageID":"msg_d7b0d14b1001sSx3cIy7aCZk0Z","sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e1ed4187d015470781cffffd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n2: \n3: **AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试**\n4: \n5: ## 1. Architecture Overview\n6: \n7: The AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library for interacting with AgentCube's Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services. The SDK follows a layered architecture:\n8: \n9: - **Public API Layer** (`agentcube/__init__.py`): Exposes `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient`\n10: - **High-Level Clients** (`code_interpreter.py`, `agent_runtime.py`): User-facing clients with business logic\n11: - **Low-Level Clients** (`clients/`): HTTP communication with control plane and data plane\n12: - **Utilities** (`utils/`): HTTP session management, logging, file I/O helpers\n13: \n14: ## 2. Package Layout\n15: \n16: ```\n17: agentcube/\n18: ├── __init__.py                    # Public exports (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n19: ├── code_interpreter.py            # CodeInterpreterClient\n20: ├── agent_runtime.py               # AgentRuntimeClient\n21: ├── exceptions.py                  # Exception hierarchy\n22: ├── clients/\n23: │   ├── __init__.py                # Re-exports data plane clients\n24: │   ├── control_plane.py          # ControlPlaneClient (Workload Manager)\n25: │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n26: │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n27: └── utils/\n28:     ├── __init__.py\n29:     ├── http.py                    # create_session\n30:     ├── utils.py                   # read_token_from_file\n31:     └── log.py                     # get_logger\n32: \n33: tests/\n34: ├── test_code_interpreter.py       # Tests for CodeInterpreterClient\n35: ├── test_agent_runtime_client.py   # Tests for AgentRuntimeClient\n36: ├── test_control_plane.py          # Tests for ControlPlaneClient\n37: ├── test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py\n38: ├── test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\n39: ├── test_http.py\n40: ├── test_utils.py\n41: └── test_exceptions.py\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ## 3. Public API Surface\n45: \n46: ### 3.1 Root Exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n47: \n48: ```python\n49: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n50: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n51: \n52: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ### 3.2 Client Exports (`agentcube/clients/__init__.py`)\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: __all__ = [\n59:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n60:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n61:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n62: ]\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## 4. Client Classes\n66: \n67: ### 4.1 CodeInterpreterClient (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n68: \n69: **Purpose**: High-level client for Code Interpreter sessions.\n70: \n71: **Constructor Parameters**:\n72: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n73: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n74: | `name` | `str` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | Session name |\n75: | `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n76: | `ttl` | `int` | `3600` | Session TTL in seconds |\n77: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Control plane URL |\n78: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Data plane router URL (required) |\n79: | `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Auth token for control plane |\n80: | `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable debug logging |\n81: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Reuse existing session |\n82: \n83: **Instance Attributes**:\n84: - `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`: Configuration values\n85: - `logger`: Logger instance\n86: - `cp_client`: ControlPlaneClient instance\n87: - `router_url`: Router URL string\n88: - `session_id`: Current session ID\n89: - `dp_client`: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient instance\n90: \n91: **Methods**:\n92: | Method | Description |\n93: |--------|-------------|\n94: | `__enter__`/`__exit__` | Context manager protocol |\n95: | `stop()` | Cleanup session and close clients |\n96: | `execute_command(command, timeout)` | Execute shell command |\n97: | `run_code(language, code, timeout)` | Run code in specified language |\n98: | `write_file(content, remote_path)` | Write file to remote session |\n99: | `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` | Upload local file |\n100: | `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` | Download remote file |\n101: | `list_files(path)` | List files in remote path |\n102: \n103: ### 4.2 AgentRuntimeClient (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n104: \n105: **Purpose**: High-level client for Agent Runtime invocations.\n106: \n107: **Constructor Parameters**:\n108: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n109: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n110: | `agent_name` | `str` | `\"my-agent\"` | Agent name |\n111: | `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n112: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Data plane router URL (required) |\n113: | `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable debug logging |\n114: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Reuse existing session |\n115: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n116: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n117: \n118: **Instance Attributes**:\n119: - `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`: Configuration\n120: - `logger`: Logger instance\n121: - `router_url`: Router URL string\n122: - `session_id`: Current session ID\n123: - `dp_client`: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient instance\n124: \n125: **Methods**:\n126: | Method | Description |\n127: |--------|-------------|\n128: | `__enter__`/`__exit__` | Context manager protocol |\n129: | `invoke(payload, timeout)` | Invoke agent with payload |\n130: | `close()` | Close client and release resources |\n131: \n132: ### 4.3 ControlPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n133: \n134: **Purpose**: Low-level client for Workload Manager (control plane) operations.\n135: \n136: **Constructor Parameters**:\n137: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n138: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n139: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Control plane URL (required) |\n140: | `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Auth token |\n141: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n142: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n143: | `pool_connections` | `int` | `10` | HTTP adapter pool connections |\n144: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | `10` | HTTP adapter pool max size |\n145: \n146: **Methods**:\n147: | Method | Description |\n148: |--------|-------------|\n149: | `create_session(name, namespace, metadata, ttl)` | Create new session, returns sessionId |\n150: | `delete_session(session_id)` | Delete session (404 returns True) |\n151: | `close()` | Close HTTP session |\n152: \n153: ### 4.4 CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n154: \n155: **Purpose**: Low-level client for Code Interpreter data plane operations.\n156: \n157: **Constructor Parameters**:\n158: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n159: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n160: | `session_id` | `str` | Required | Session identifier |\n161: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL |\n162: | `namespace` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Namespace |\n163: | `cr_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Custom resource name |\n164: | `base_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Explicit base URL |\n165: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n166: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n167: \n168: **Methods**:\n169: | Method | Description |\n170: |--------|-------------|\n171: | `execute_command(command, timeout)` | Execute shell command |\n172: | `run_code(language, code, timeout)` | Run code |\n173: | `write_file(content, remote_path)` | Write file (base64) |\n174: | `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` | Upload file (multipart) |\n175: | `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` | Download file (stream) |\n176: | `list_files(path)` | List files |\n177: | `close()` | Close HTTP session |\n178: \n179: ### 4.5 AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n180: \n181: **Purpose**: Low-level client for Agent Runtime data plane operations.\n182: \n183: **Class Constant**:\n184: - `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n185: \n186: **Constructor Parameters**:\n187: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n188: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n189: | `router_url` | `str` | Required | Router URL |\n190: | `namespace` | `str` | Required | Namespace |\n191: | `agent_name` | `str` | Required | Agent name |\n192: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n193: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n194: \n195: **Methods**:\n196: | Method | Description |\n197: |--------|-------------|\n198: | `bootstrap_session_id()` | GET to fetch session ID from header |\n199: | `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` | POST JSON payload |\n200: | `close()` | Close HTTP session |\n201: \n202: ## 5. HTTP API Contracts\n203: \n204: ### 5.1 Control Plane (Workload Manager)\n205: \n206: | Method | Path | Body | Response |\n207: |--------|------|------|----------|\n208: | `POST` | `/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | `{\"sessionId\": \"...\"}` |\n209: | `DELETE` | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | — | 200 or 404 (treated as success) |\n210: \n211: **Headers**:\n212: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n213: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token provided)\n214: \n215: ### 5.2 Data Plane — Code Interpreter\n216: \n217: **Base URL Construction**:\n218: ```\n219: {router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\n220: ```\n221: \n222: | Method | Relative Path | Body | Notes |\n223: |--------|---------------|------|-------|\n224: | `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Read timeout = timeout + 2s |\n225: | `POST` | `api/files` (JSON) | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | |\n226: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` | |\n227: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | — | Stream for download |\n228: | `GET` | `api/files?path=...` | — | List files |\n229: \n230: **Headers**:\n231: - Default: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n232: - JSON: `Content-Type: application/json`\n233: \n234: ### 5.3 Data Plane — Agent Runtime\n235: \n236: **Base URL Construction**:\n237: ```\n238: {router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n239: ```\n240: \n241: | Method | Path | Headers | Body |\n242: |--------|------|---------|------|\n243: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | — |\n244: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | JSON payload |\n245: \n246: ## 6. Configuration Resolution\n247: \n248: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed:\n249: \n250: | Component | Resolved from |\n251: |-----------|---------------|\n252: | ControlPlaneClient base_url | `workload_manager_url` arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n253: | ControlPlaneClient auth | `auth_token` arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n254: | CodeInterpreterClient router_url | `router_url` arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n255: | AgentRuntimeClient router_url | `router_url` arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n256: | Default timeouts | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` for all clients |\n257: | Pool settings | `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n258: \n259: ## 7. Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n260: \n261: ```python\n262: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n263:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n264: \n265: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n266:     exit_code: int\n267:     stderr: str\n268:     command: Optional[str]\n269: \n270: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n271:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation/management fails\"\"\"\n272: \n273: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n274:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ## 8. Utility Functions\n278: \n279: ### 8.1 `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n280: \n281: Creates `requests.Session` with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\n282: \n283: ### 8.2 `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n284: \n285: Reads file contents as token string. Returns `None` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n286: \n287: ### 8.3 `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n288: \n289: Returns `logging.Logger` with configurable level (INFO default, DEBUG if verbose).\n290: \n291: ## 9. Testing Strategy\n292: \n293: ### 9.1 Test Framework\n294: \n295: - **pytest** with **pytest-mock** for mocking\n296: - **pytest-asyncio** for async tests\n297: - **pytest-cov** for coverage\n298: \n299: ### 9.2 Test Organization\n300: \n301: Tests mirror the source structure:\n302: - `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` — High-level client tests\n303: - `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` — High-level client tests\n304: - `tests/test_control_plane.py` — Control plane HTTP tests\n305: - `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — Data plane HTTP tests\n306: - `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — Data plane HTTP tests\n307: - `tests/test_http.py` — HTTP utility tests\n308: - `tests/test_utils.py` — Utility function tests\n309: - `tests/test_exceptions.py` — Exception hierarchy tests\n310: \n311: ### 9.3 Test Patterns\n312: \n313: **Unit Tests**: Mock HTTP responses to test client logic without network calls.\n314: \n315: **Integration Points**:\n316: - Environment variable resolution (ROUTER_URL, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL)\n317: - Token file reading from Kubernetes service account path\n318: - Context manager lifecycle (enter/exit)\n319: - Session bootstrap via GET request\n320: \n321: **Error Scenarios**:\n322: - Non-zero exit codes → CommandExecutionError\n323: - Missing session headers → ValueError\n324: - Network failures → SessionError/DataPlaneError\n325: - 404 on delete → Returns True (success)\n326: \n327: ### 9.4 Coverage Areas\n328: \n329: | Component | Coverage |\n330: |-----------|----------|\n331: | CodeInterpreterClient | Constructor, context manager, execute_command, run_code, file operations, stop |\n332: | AgentRuntimeClient | Constructor, bootstrap, invoke, close |\n333: | ControlPlaneClient | Create session, delete session (404 handling), auth headers |\n334: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | URL construction, execute, run_code, files API, download, list |\n335: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | Bootstrap, invoke, timeout handling |\n336: | Utils | HTTP session, logger, token reading |\n337: | Exceptions | All exception classes and attributes |\n338: \n339: ## 10. Dependencies\n340: \n341: ```toml\n342: dependencies = [\n343:     \"requests\",\n344:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n345:     \"cryptography\",\n346: ]\n347: ```\n348: \n349: Build requirements:\n350: - `setuptools>=61.0`\n351: - `wheel`\n352: - Python >=3.10\n353: \n354: ## 11. Acceptance Criteria Verification\n355: \n356: | Requirement | Verified By |\n357: |-------------|-------------|\n358: | CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle | `test_context_manager`, `test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup`, `test_stop_closes_clients` |\n359: | AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle | `test_context_manager`, `test_bootstrap_session`, `test_close` |\n360: | HTTP client contracts | `test_create_session_success`, `test_delete_session_not_found`, `test_execute_command`, `test_invoke` |\n361: | Session header management | `test_constructor_session_header`, `test_session_header_constant` |\n362: | Exception hierarchy | `test_command_execution_error_attributes`, `test_session_error_inherits`, `test_data_plane_error_inherits` |\n363: | Timeout behavior | `test_execute_command_with_timeout`, `test_invoke_timeout_tuple` |\n\n(End of file - total 363 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\n**AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试**\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library for interacting with AgentCube's Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services. The SDK follows a layered architecture:\n\n- **Public API Layer** (`agentcube/__init__.py`): Exposes `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient`\n- **High-Level Clients** (`code_interpreter.py`, `agent_runtime.py`): User-facing clients with business logic\n- **Low-Level Clients** (`clients/`): HTTP communication with control plane and data plane\n- **Utilities** (`utils/`): HTTP session management, logging, file I/O helpers\n\n## 2. Package Layout\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── __init__.py                    # Public exports (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n├── code_interpreter.py            # CodeInterpreterClient\n├── agent_runtime.py               # AgentRuntimeClient","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775885953043,"end":1775885953067}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775885953106,"sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0d282e001J06nH5kLvYr6Ch","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b0d14b1001sSx3cIy7aCZk0Z","sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19854,"input":4912,"output":100,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":14842}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775885956742,"sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0d3684001tC1wxClcSndUEB","messageID":"msg_d7b0d2871001xYF306kPLkjC0b","sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885958080,"sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0d389b001yRxa2eRW9h3Qhc","messageID":"msg_d7b0d2871001xYF306kPLkjC0b","sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b223b3aac47c4998bdfd2e4b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-042 — Docusaurus Documentation Site Framework\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Establish a Docusaurus-based documentation site framework for the agentcube project to provide a modern, searchable, and versioned documentation platform. This framework will enable the team to maintain comprehensive documentation including API references, tutorials, architecture guides, and contributor guidelines in a scalable and maintainable manner.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### In scope\n10: \n11: | Item | Detail |\n12: |------|--------|\n13: | **Module path** | `docs` |\n14: | **Language** | TypeScript |\n15: | **Framework** | Docusaurus 3.x |\n16: | **Documentation types** | API docs, guides, tutorials, changelog, blog |\n17: | **Versioning** | Multi-version support for releases |\n18: | **Deployment target** | Static site generation for GitHub Pages or similar |\n19: \n20: ### Out of scope\n21: \n22: - Content authoring for specific documentation pages\n23: - CI/CD pipeline integration for deployment\n24: - Search backend configuration (Algolia DocSearch)\n25: - Custom React components beyond Docusaurus defaults\n26: - Internationalization (i18n) setup\n27: - Translation workflows\n28: \n29: ### Dependencies\n30: \n31: | Dependency | Usage |\n32: |------------|-------|\n33: | `docusaurus` | Core documentation framework |\n34: | `@docusaurus/preset-classic` | Classic preset with docs, blog, pages |\n35: | `@docusaurus/theme-classic` | Default theme |\n36: | `@mdx-js/react` | MDX support for React in Markdown |\n37: | `react`, `react-dom` | UI library |\n38: \n39: ## Design\n40: \n41: ### Directory structure\n42: \n43: ```\n44: docs/\n45: ├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus configuration\n46: ├── sidebars.ts                    # Sidebar configuration\n47: ├── tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript configuration\n48: ├── package.json                   # Node dependencies\n49: ├── package-lock.json\n50: ├── static/                        # Static assets\n51: │   ├── img/                       # Images\n52: │   └── favicon.ico\n53: ├── docs/                          # Documentation files (Markdown/MDX)\n54: │   ├── index.md                   # Landing page\n55: │   ├── getting-started/          # Getting started guides\n56: │   ├── guides/                    # User guides\n57: │   ├── api/                       # API reference\n58: │   └── contributed/               # Contributor guidelines\n59: ├── blog/                          # Blog posts (optional)\n60: │   └── index.md\n61: ├── src/                           # Custom React components\n62: │   ├── css/\n63: │   │   └── custom.css            # Custom styles\n64: │   └── pages/                    # Custom pages\n65: │       └── index.tsx             # Landing page component\n66: ├── versioned_docs/                # Versioned documentation\n67: │   └── version-1.0.0/\n68: ├── versioned_sidebars/            # Sidebars for versions\n69: └── scripts/                      # Build/deploy scripts\n70:     └── build.sh\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ### Docusaurus configuration\n74: \n75: ```typescript\n76: // docusaurus.config.ts\n77: import { themes as prismThemes } from 'prism-react-renderer';\n78: import type { Config } from '@docusaurus/types';\n79: import type * as Preset from '@docusaurus/preset-classic';\n80: \n81: const config: Config = {\n82:   title: 'AgentCube',\n83:   tagline: 'Intelligent Agent Runtime Platform',\n84:   url: 'https://agentcube.io',\n85:   baseUrl: '/',\n86:   onBrokenLinks: 'throw',\n87:   onBrokenMarkdownLinks: 'warn',\n88:   favicon: 'img/favicon.ico',\n89:   organizationName: 'volcano-sh',\n90:   projectName: 'agentcube',\n91: \n92:   presets: [\n93:     [\n94:       'classic',\n95:       {\n96:         docs: {\n97:           sidebarPath: './sidebars.ts',\n98:           docVersionSuggestions: true,\n99:           showLastUpdateAuthor: true,\n100:           showLastUpdateTime: true,\n101:         },\n102:         blog: {\n103:           showReadingTime: true,\n104:           blogSidebarCount: 'ALL',\n105:           blogSidebarTitle: 'All Posts',\n106:         },\n107:         theme: {\n108:           customCss: './src/css/custom.css',\n109:         },\n110:       } satisfies Preset.Options,\n111:     ],\n112:   ],\n113: \n114:   themeConfig: {\n115:     image: 'img/social-card.png',\n116:     navbar: {\n117:       title: 'AgentCube',\n118:       logo: {\n119:         alt: 'AgentCube Logo',\n120:         src: 'img/logo.svg',\n121:       },\n122:       items: [\n123:         {\n124:           type: 'docSidebar',\n125:           sidebarId: 'docsSidebar',\n126:           position: 'left',\n127:           label: 'Docs',\n128:         },\n129:         {\n130:           type: 'docsVersionDropdown',\n131:           position: 'right',\n132:         },\n133:         {\n134:           href: 'https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube',\n135:           label: 'GitHub',\n136:           position: 'right',\n137:         },\n138:       ],\n139:     },\n140:     footer: {\n141:       style: 'dark',\n142:       copyright: `Copyright © ${new Date().getFullYear()} Volcano.sh`,\n143:     },\n144:     prism: {\n145:       theme: prismThemes.github,\n146:       darkTheme: prismThemes.dracula,\n147:     },\n148:   } satisfies Preset.ThemeConfig,\n149: };\n150: \n151: export default config;\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### Sidebar configuration\n155: \n156: ```typescript\n157: // sidebars.ts\n158: import type { SidebarsConfig } from '@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs';\n159: \n160: const sidebars: SidebarsConfig = {\n161:   docsSidebar: [\n162:     'intro',\n163:     {\n164:       type: 'category',\n165:       label: 'Getting Started',\n166:       collapsed: false,\n167:       items: ['getting-started/installation', 'getting-started/quickstart'],\n168:     },\n169:     {\n170:       type: 'category',\n171:       label: 'Guides',\n172:       items: [\n173:         'guides/architecture',\n174:         'guides/configuration',\n175:         'guides/monitoring',\n176:       ],\n177:     },\n178:     {\n179:       type: 'category',\n180:       label: 'API Reference',\n181:       items: [\n182:         'api/agent-runtime',\n183:         'api/code-interpreter',\n184:         'api/cli',\n185:       ],\n186:     },\n187:     {\n188:       type: 'category',\n189:       label: 'Contributing',\n190:       items: [\n191:         'contributed/overview',\n192:         'contributed/development',\n193:         'contributed/coding-standards',\n194:       ],\n195:     },\n196:   ],\n197: };\n198: \n199: export default sidebars;\n200: ```\n201: \n202: ### Package.json scripts\n203: \n204: ```json\n205: {\n206:   \"scripts\": {\n207:     \"docusaurus\": \"docusaurus\",\n208:     \"start\": \"docusaurus start\",\n209:     \"build\": \"docusaurus build\",\n210:     \"deploy\": \"docusaurus deploy\",\n211:     \"clear\": \"docusaurus clear\",\n212:     \"serve\": \"docusaurus serve\",\n213:     \"write-translations\": \"docusaurus write-translations\",\n214:     \"write-heading-ids\": \"docusaurus write-heading-ids\"\n215:   }\n216: }\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### Custom CSS example\n220: \n221: ```css\n222: /* src/css/custom.css */\n223: :root {\n224:   --ifm-color-primary: #3b82f6;\n225:   --ifm-color-primary-dark: #2563eb;\n226:   --ifm-color-primary-darker: #1d4ed8;\n227:   --ifm-color-primary-darkest: #1e40af;\n228:   --ifm-color-primary-light: #60a5fa;\n229:   --ifm-color-primary-lighter: #93c5fd;\n230:   --ifm-color-primary-lightest: #bfdbfe;\n231:   --ifm-code-font-size: 95%;\n232: }\n233: \n234: .navbar__title {\n235:   font-weight: 700;\n236: }\n237: \n238: .admonition {\n239:   font-size: 0.9rem;\n240: }\n241: ```\n242: \n243: ## Impact analysis\n244: \n245: ### Files created\n246: \n247: | File | Description |\n248: |------|-------------|\n249: | `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` | Docusaurus configuration (~80 lines) |\n250: | `docs/sidebars.ts` | Sidebar navigation config (~40 lines) |\n251: | `docs/tsconfig.json` | TypeScript config (~20 lines) |\n252: | `docs/package.json` | Node dependencies (~40 lines) |\n253: | `docs/package-lock.json` | Lock file |\n254: | `docs/static/*` | Static assets (~5 files) |\n255: | `docs/docs/intro.md` | Introduction page (~30 lines) |\n256: | `docs/docs/getting-started/*.md` | Getting started guides (~100 lines) |\n257: | `docs/docs/guides/*.md` | User guides (~150 lines) |\n258: | `docs/docs/api/*.md` | API reference templates (~100 lines) |\n259: | `docs/docs/contributed/*.md` | Contributor guidelines (~100 lines) |\n260: | `docs/src/css/custom.css` | Custom styles (~50 lines) |\n261: | `docs/src/pages/index.tsx` | Landing page (~80 lines) |\n262: \n263: **Estimated total**: ~800 lines\n264: \n265: ### Files modified\n266: \n267: | File | Change |\n268: |------|--------|\n269: | `.gitignore` | Add docs/build, docs/node_modules |\n270: | `README.md` | Add docs site link |\n271: \n272: ### Dependencies\n273: \n274: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n275: |------------|---------|---------|\n276: | @docusaurus/core | ^3.0.0 | Core framework |\n277: | @docusaurus/preset-classic | ^3.0.0 | Preset with docs/blog |\n278: | @docusaurus/theme-classic | ^3.0.0 | Default theme |\n279: | @mdx-js/react | ^3.0.0 | MDX support |\n280: | react | ^18.2.0 | React library |\n281: | react-dom | ^18.2.0 | React DOM |\n282: \n283: ### Downstream consumers\n284: \n285: | Consumer | Dependency |\n286: |----------|-----------|\n287: | Developers | Use docs for onboarding and reference |\n288: | Users | Self-service documentation |\n289: | Support team | Reference for troubleshooting |\n290: | Marketing | Product documentation |\n291: \n292: ### Breaking change risk\n293: \n294: **Very Low**: This is a new documentation module. No existing code is modified. The documentation site is additive and does not affect the core product functionality.\n295: \n296: ### Performance characteristics\n297: \n298: - **Build time**: ~1-3 minutes for full site\n299: - **Dev server startup**: ~10-20 seconds\n300: - **Static site size**: ~10-50MB depending on content\n301: - **Page load**: Fast with static generation + optional CDN\n302: \n303: ### Edge cases handled\n304: \n305: 1. **Broken links**: Docusaurus validates links during build\n306: 2. **Missing images**: Graceful fallback for missing assets\n307: 3. **Version conflicts**: Explicit version management\n308: 4. **Build failures**: Clear error messages for authoring issues\n309: 5. **Mobile responsiveness**: Built-in responsive design\n310: \n311: ## Alternatives considered\n312: \n313: ### 1. Use GitBook\n314: \n315: **Approach**: Use GitBook platform for documentation.\n316: \n317: **Rejected because**:\n318: - Proprietary SaaS with limited customization\n319: - Free tier restrictions on collaborators\n320: - Less control over hosting and branding\n321: - Integration requires GitHub OAuth\n322: \n323: ### 2. Use MkDocs with Material theme\n324: \n325: **Approach**: Use MkDocs (Python) with Material for MkDocs theme.\n326: \n327: **Rejected because**:\n328: - Python-based (team more familiar with Node.js/TypeScript)\n329: - MDX not supported natively (limited React component embedding)\n330: - Static site generation less flexible for React integrations\n331: - Team preference for JavaScript ecosystem\n332: \n333: ### 3. Use VuePress / VitePress\n334: \n335: **Approach**: Use VuePress or VitePress (Vue-based documentation frameworks).\n336: \n337: **Rejected because**:\n338: - Vue ecosystem (team works with React)\n339: - Docusaurus has better integration with React-based projects\n340: - Docusaurus has mature multi-version support\n341: - Docusaurus is the standard for Meta/Facebook ecosystem projects\n342: \n343: ### 4. Use plain Markdown with GitHub Pages\n344: \n345: **Approach**: Use raw Markdown files with GitHub Pages (Jekyll).\n346: \n347: **Rejected because**:\n348: - Limited navigation and search functionality\n349: - No built-in versioning support\n350: - Poor mobile experience\n351: - Manual navigation structure management\n352: - No React component support in MDX\n353: \n354: ### 5. Use Next.js with next-mdx-remote\n355: \n356: **Approach**: Build custom docs site with Next.js and MDX.\n357: \n358: **Rejected because**:\n359: - Significant development overhead\n360: - Custom implementation required for features Docusaurus provides out-of-box\n361: - Higher maintenance burden\n362: - Versioning requires custom implementation\n363: - Team preference for purpose-built solution\n364: \n365: ### 6. Use Hugo with Docsy theme\n366: \n367: **Approach**: Use Hugo static site generator with Docsy theme.\n368: \n369: **Rejected because**:\n370: - Go template ecosystem (team not familiar with)\n371: - MDX support limited\n372: - Less React integration capability\n373: - More complex theming customization\n\n(End of file - total 373 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-042 — Docusaurus Documentation Site Framework\n\n## Purpose\n\nEstablish a Docusaurus-based documentation site framework for the agentcube project to provide a modern, searchable, and versioned documentation platform. This framework will enable the team to maintain comprehensive documentation including API references, tutorials, architecture guides, and contributor guidelines in a scalable and maintainable manner.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `docs` |\n| **Language** | TypeScript |\n| **Framework** | Docusaurus 3.x |\n| **Documentation types** | API docs, guides, tutorials, changelog, blog |\n| **Versioning** | Multi-version support for releases |\n| **Deployment target** | Static site generation for GitHub Pages or similar |\n\n### Out of scope","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775885958069,"end":1775885958078}}}}
