{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775885962277,"sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0d4c23001Sr3GouobXPJ4Mu","messageID":"msg_d7b0d3bf7001im9FFyCU80CuW5","sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886015731,"sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0d537a001BXQ7dhNMwLM1yo","messageID":"msg_d7b0d3bf7001im9FFyCU80CuW5","sessionID":"ses_284f2ffadffevIQseaBohSvRlj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_dfcf3b3b54dd490b9e4dd22f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-042 — Docusaurus Documentation Site Framework\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\nThe AgentCube documentation site is a Docusaurus-based static documentation platform with the following architectural layers:\n\n- **Build Layer**: Docusaurus CLI and build system (Node.js/TypeScript)\n- **Content Layer**: Markdown/MDX documentation files organized by category\n- **Presentation Layer**: Docusaurus React theme components\n- **Deployment Layer**: Static site generation output for hosting\n\n## 2. Module Structure\n\n```\ndocs/\n├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus configuration (Config interface)\n├── sidebars.ts                    # Sidebar navigation (SidebarsConfig)\n├── tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript configuration\n├── package.json                   # Node dependencies and scripts\n├── package-lock.json\n├── static/                        # Static assets\n│   ├── img/\n│   │   ├── logo.svg\n│   │   ├── favicon.ico\n│   │   └── social-card.png\n│   └── robots.txt\n├── docs/                          # Documentation source files\n│   ├── index.md                   # Landing page\n│   ├── getting-started/\n│   │   ├── installation.md\n│   │   └── quickstart.md\n│   ├── guides/\n│   │   ├── architecture.md\n│   │   ├── configuration.md\n│   │   └── monitoring.md\n│   ├── api/\n│   │   ├── agent-runtime.md\n│   │   ├── code-interpreter.md\n│   │   └── cli.md\n│   └── contributed/\n│       ├── overview.md\n│       ├── development.md\n│       └── coding-standards.md\n├── blog/                          # Blog posts (optional)\n├── src/\n│   ├── css/\n│   │   └── custom.css            # Custom theme overrides\n│   ├── pages/\n│   │   ├── index.tsx             # Custom landing page\n│   │   └── index.module.css\n│   └── theme/\n│       └── Footer                # Custom footer component\n├── versioned_docs/                # Versioned documentation\n│   └── version-1.0.0/\n├── versioned_sidebars/            # Sidebars for versions\n├── versioned_blog/                # Versioned blog posts\n└── scripts/\n    └── build.sh                  # Build script\n```\n\n## 3. Data Structures\n\n### 3.1 Docusaurus Configuration\n\n```typescript\n// docusaurus.config.ts types (from @docusaurus/types)\n\ninterface Config {\n  title: string;\n  tagline?: string;\n  url: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  onBrokenLinks?: 'throw' | 'warn' | 'ignore';\n  onBrokenMarkdownLinks?: 'throw' | 'warn' | 'ignore';\n  favicon?: string;\n  organizationName?: string;\n  projectName?: string;\n  presets?: Preset[];\n  themeConfig?: ThemeConfig;\n  plugins?: Plugin[];\n  themes?: Theme[];\n  markdown?: MarkdownConfig;\n}\n\ninterface ThemeConfig {\n  image?: string;\n  navbar?: Navbar;\n  footer?: Footer;\n  prism?: PrismThemeConfig;\n  announcementBar?: AnnouncementBar;\n  colorMode?: ColorModeConfig;\n  docs?: DocsThemeConfig;\n  tableOfContents?: TableOfContentsConfig;\n}\n\ninterface Navbar {\n  title?: string;\n  logo?: {\n    src: string;\n    alt?: string;\n    href?: string;\n  };\n  items: NavbarItem[];\n  hideOnScroll?: boolean;\n}\n\ntype NavbarItem = \n  | { type: 'doc'; docId: string; label: string; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n  | { type: 'docSidebar'; sidebarId: string; label: string; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n  | { type: 'docsVersionDropdown'; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n  | { type: 'localeDropdown'; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n  | { type: 'search' }\n  | { type: 'href'; href: string; label: string; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n  | { type: 'html'; html: string; position: 'left' | 'right' };\n\ninterface Footer {\n  style: 'light' | 'dark';\n  links?: FooterLink[];\n  copyright?: string;\n  logo?: {\n    src: string;\n    alt?: string;\n    href?: string;\n  };\n}\n\ninterface FooterLink {\n  title?: string;\n  items: FooterItem[];\n}\n\ninterface FooterItem {\n  label: string;\n  href?: string;\n  to?: string;\n  docId?: string;\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Sidebar Configuration\n\n```typescript\n// sidebars.ts types (from @docusaurus/plugin-content-docs)\n\ninterface SidebarsConfig {\n  [sidebarId: string]: SidebarItem[];\n}\n\ntype SidebarItem = \n  | string  // Document ID\n  | {\n      type: 'category';\n      label: string;\n      items: SidebarItem[];\n      collapsed?: boolean;\n      collapsible?: boolean;\n      className?: string;\n    }\n  | {\n      type: 'autogenerated';\n      dirName: string;\n    }\n  | {\n      type: 'link';\n      label: string;\n      href: string;\n    }\n  | {\n      type: 'ref';\n      id: string;\n    };\n```\n\n### 3.3 Document Frontmatter\n\n```typescript\n// Standard frontmatter for docs\n\ninterface DocFrontmatter {\n  id?: string;\n  title: string;\n  description?: string;\n  sidebar_label?: string;\n  sidebar_position?: number;\n  hide_title?: boolean;\n  hide_table_of_contents?: boolean;\n  tags?: string[];\n  image?: string;\n  keywords?: string[];\n  draft?: boolean;\n  slug?: string;\n}\n```\n\n## 4. API Contracts\n\n### 4.1 Docusaurus CLI Commands\n\n| Command | Description | Output |\n|---------|-------------|--------|\n| `npm run start` | Start dev server (hot reload) | `http://localhost:3000` |\n| `npm run build` | Build static site | `build/` directory |\n| `npm run deploy` | Deploy to GitHub Pages | GitHub Pages |\n| `npm run serve` | Serve built site locally | `http://localhost:3000` |\n| `npm run clear` | Clear Docusaurus cache | Removes `.docusaurus/` |\n| `docusaurus write-translations` | Generate translation files | `i18n/` directory |\n| `docusaurus write-heading-ids` | Generate heading IDs | Updates MD files |\n\n### 4.2 Build Output Structure\n\n```\nbuild/\n├── index.html                    # Landing page\n├── docs/\n│   ├── intro/index.html\n│   ├── getting-started/\n│   │   ├── installation/index.html\n│   │   └── quickstart/index.html\n│   └── ...\n├── blog/\n│   └── index.html\n├── img/\n│   ├── logo.svg\n│   └── favicon.ico\n├── css/\n│   └── styles.css\n├── js/\n│   └── main.js\n└── 404.html                      # Not found page\n```\n\n### 4.3 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Default |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `NODE_ENV` | Build environment | `development` |\n| `GIT_USER` | GitHub username for deployment | — |\n| `USE_SSH` | Use SSH for GitHub deploy | `false` |\n\n## 5. Error Handling\n\n### 5.1 Build-Time Errors\n\n| Error | Cause | Resolution |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| `Error: Docusaurus node version mismatch` | Node.js version incompatible | Use Node.js 18+ |\n| `Error: Broken link detected` | Invalid internal link | Fix link in MD file |\n| `Error: Build failed due to parsing errors` | Invalid MDX/React syntax | Check MDX content |\n| `Error: Module not found` | Missing dependency | Run `npm install` |\n\n### 5.2 Validation During Build\n\nDocusaurus performs automatic validation:\n\n1. **Link Validation**: `onBrokenLinks` config option\n   - `'throw'`: Fail build on broken links\n   - `'warn'`: Log warning, continue build\n   - `'ignore'`: Skip validation\n\n2. **Markdown Validation**: `onBrokenMarkdownLinks` config option\n\n3. **TypeScript Validation**: Via `tsc` during build\n\n### 5.3 Common Issues\n\n| Issue | Solution |\n|-------|----------|\n| Slow hot reload | Run `npm run clear` |\n| Stale content | Clear browser cache or disable SWC cache |\n| CSS not applying | Check `custom.css` syntax |\n| Sidebar not showing | Verify `sidebars.ts` structure |\n| Version dropdown missing | Add version with `npm run docusaurus docs:version` |\n\n## 6. Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Test Framework\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `npm run build` | Validate build process |\n| `npm run start` | Validate dev server |\n| `eslint` | Lint TypeScript and React |\n| `prettier` | Format check for MD/MDX |\n\n### 6.2 Validation Tests\n\n| Test | Command | Success Criteria |\n|------|---------|------------------|\n| Build | `npm run build` | Exit code 0, `build/` exists |\n| Dev server | `npm run start` | Server starts without errors |\n| Link check | Build with `onBrokenLinks: 'throw'` | No broken link errors |\n| Type check | `npx tsc --noEmit` | No TypeScript errors |\n| Lint | `npx eslint .` | No lint errors |\n| Format | `npx prettier --check .` | No format violations |\n\n### 6.3 Content Validation\n\n| Check | Implementation |\n|-------|----------------|\n| Frontmatter completeness | Required fields: `title` |\n| Code block syntax | Prism highlighting validation |\n| Image references | File existence check |\n| Internal links | Docusaurus link validation |\n| Heading hierarchy | MDX linting rules |\n\n### 6.4 Browser Testing\n\n| Environment | Target |\n|-------------|--------|\n| Chrome/Edge | Latest |\n| Firefox | Latest |\n| Safari | Latest |\n| Mobile viewport | 375px width |\n\n### 6.5 CI Integration\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/docs.yml\nname: Documentation\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    paths: ['docs/**']\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n        with:\n          node-version: '18'\n      - run: npm ci\n      - run: npm run build\n      - run: npm run lint\n```\n\n## 7. Dependencies\n\n### 7.1 Core Dependencies\n\n```json\n{\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.7.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.7.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/theme-classic\": \"^3.7.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/theme-common\": \"^3.7.0\",\n    \"@mdx-js/react\": \"^3.0.0\",\n    \"clsx\": \"^2.1.0\",\n    \"prism-react-renderer\": \"^2.3.0\",\n    \"react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n    \"react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 7.2 Dev Dependencies\n\n```json\n{\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/module-type-aliases\": \"^3.7.0\",\n    \"@types/react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n    \"@types/react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.0\",\n    \"prettier\": \"^3.2.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.3.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## 8. Configuration Summary\n\n| Configuration File | Purpose |\n|--------------------|---------|\n| `docusaurus.config.ts` | Site metadata, presets, theme config |\n| `sidebars.ts` | Navigation structure |\n| `tsconfig.json` | TypeScript options |\n| `src/css/custom.css` | Theme customization |\n| `.eslintrc.js` | Linting rules |\n| `.prettierrc` | Code formatting |\n\n## 9. Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Requirement | Verification |\n|-------------|--------------|\n| Dev server starts | `npm run start` succeeds |\n| Static build succeeds | `npm run build` produces `build/` |\n| All docs render | Manual browser check |\n| Navigation works | Click all sidebar items |\n| Version dropdown | At least one version exists |\n| Responsive design | Test mobile viewport |\n| 404 page works | Navigate to invalid URL |\n| No console errors | Check browser DevTools |","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775886015618,"end":1775886015728}}}}
